Drop columns with no data and drop rows including NaN¶

In [4]:
df_pop = df_pop.drop(columns=['Indicator Name', 'Indicator Code', '2018', 'Unnamed: 63'])
df_pop = df_pop.dropna(axis=0)
print(df_pop.shape)

Convert values in Mega¶

In [5]:
df_popM = df_pop.copy()
df_popM.loc[:, '1960':'2017'] /= 1000000

# find the line corresponding to max population
display(df_popM.loc[df_popM['2017'].idxmax(), ['Country Name', '2017']])

Cleanup data¶

This data includes area/world data, so remove them
地域ごとの合計値が含まれているようなので、多すぎるデータは削除

In [6]:

Data seems to be OK, so write them to new CSV file¶

This cleaned CSV file will be useful for additional analysis.
次の解析のために、きれいにしたCSVファイルを保存しておく。　　

In [7]:
df_popM.to_csv(csv_out, index=False)

Make choropleth map¶

In [8]:
m = folium.Map(location=[48,-10], zoom_start=1)
display(m)
In [9]:
folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=geo,
    key_on='feature.properties.gu_a3',
    data=df_popM,
    columns=['Country Code', '2017'],
    fill_color='BuPu',
    legend_name='Population (M) 2017'
).add_to(m)

display(m)

Save to html file¶

In [10]:
m.save(outfile=html_out)
